manifest.name: Calls
manifest.description: Integrates real-time voice communication in Mattermost

settings.help_text: The IP (or hostname) to be used as the host ICE candidate. If empty, it defaults to resolving via STUN.
The UDP port the RTC server will listen on.
A comma separated list of ICE servers URLs (STUN/TURN) to use.
When set to true, it allows channel admins to enable or disable calls in their channels. It also allows participants of DMs/GMs to enable or disable calls.
When set to true, calls will be possible in all channels where they are not explicitly disabled.
